54
00:04:13,759 --> 00:04:17,759
They thought it could be a niche product that might not sell, but really caught the public's

55
00:04:17,759 --> 00:04:23,279
imagination in every market that it was offered in. When the Walkman was sold to the rest of the world

56
00:04:23,279 --> 00:04:27,439
and became popular with youngsters, people thought it was a niche product.

57
00:04:27,439 --> 00:04:30,719
Something marketed for sale to a small specific group.

58
00:04:30,719 --> 00:04:36,159
But instead, people of all ages began wearing Walkmans to listen to their favourite music on the move.

59
00:04:36,719 --> 00:04:39,759
And the new invention caught the public imagination.

60
00:04:39,759 --> 00:04:44,560
An idiom meaning made the public interested in or excited about something.

61
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:49,599
Many put the Walkman success down to its perfect combination of sound quality,

62
00:04:49,599 --> 00:04:52,399
small size and affordable price.

63
00:04:52,399 --> 00:04:56,319
But exactly how affordable Georgina remember my quiz question?

64
00:04:56,319 --> 00:05:02,480
Yes Neil, you asked how much the original Walkman cost when it came out in 1979.

65
00:05:02,480 --> 00:05:03,599
What did you say?

66
00:05:03,599 --> 00:05:06,079
I thought it cost B$100.

67
00:05:06,879 --> 00:05:11,199
Well Georgina things were cheaper in 1979, but not that cheap.

68
00:05:11,199 --> 00:05:14,560
The actual price was C$150.

69
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:17,439
That's around $530 today.

70
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:21,839
In this programme we've been looking back at the iconic Sony Walkman.

71
